On Veterans Day, Vice President Mike Pence gave a speech at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson in Anchorage, Alaska, where he thanked the military personnel for their service. He mentioned that President Trump paid his respects at an American cemetery in Paris and joined world leaders to remember Armistice Day. Pence emphasized that the nation will never forget the service and sacrifice of the men and women of the armed forces. He also highlighted the importance of Veterans Day and asked all veterans in the room to stand and be recognized. Pence praised President Trump for being a strong advocate for veterans and mentioned the passage of legislation to improve healthcare and accountability at the VA. He also pledged to provide the necessary resources and support for the military to accomplish their mission and come home safely. Pence expressed gratitude to the families of the servicemen and servicewomen and concluded by thanking everyone for their service and wishing them a happy Veterans Day.